{ By Reuters   Published:  19:19, 29 June 2019   https://www.dailymail.co.uk//wires/reuters/article-7196109/Maple-Leafs-sign-G-Hutchinson-D-Marincin.html }
The Toronto Maple Leafs signed goaltender Michael Hutchinson and defenseman Martin Marincin to one-year contracts. The team said each contract is valued at $700,000. The Maple Leafs acquired Hutchinson, 29, from the Florida Panthers in a trade on Dec. 29. He appeared in five games with Toronto and 23 with the Toronto Marlies of the American Hockey League. With the Maple Leafs, he was 2-3-0 with a 2.64 goals-against average and .914 save percentage. In 111 career NHL games with the Maple Leafs, Winnipeg Jets (2013-18) and Panthers (2018), Hutchinson has posted a 46-43-0 record with a 2.70 GAA, .908 save percentage and four shutouts. An Ontario native, Hutchinson was a third-round selection of the Boston Bruins in the 2008 NHL Draft. Marincin, 27, appeared in 24 games last season for the Maple Leafs, scoring one goal and four assists. A second-round selection of the Edmonton Oilers in the 2010 draft, he debuted with Edmonton in 2013 and spent two seasons there before being traded to Toronto following the 2014-15 season. He has 30 points (four goals, 26 assists) in 201 regular-season games in his career. --Field Level Media 
